      "stem": "The graphs of the equations \\(y=3x-5\\) and \\(y = \\frac{1}{3}x\\) intersect how many times in the \\(xy\\)-plane?",

      "choices": [
        "\\(0\\)",
        "\\(1\\)",
        "\\(2\\)",
        "\\(3\\)"
      ],

      "answerIndex": 1,

      "explanation": "<div class='explanation-step'>Add the two equations to eliminate \\(y\\).</div><div class='explanation-math'>$$\\begin{aligned}(x+y)+(x-y) &= 5+1 \\\\ 2x &= 6 \\\\ x &= 3\\end{aligned}$$</div><div class='explanation-step'>Substitute \\(x=3\\) into \\(x+y=5\\).</div><div class='explanation-math'>$$3+y=5 \\Rightarrow y=2$$</div><div class='explanation-step'>The solution is \\((3,2)\\).</div>"
    },

